WEBVTT

00:06.040 --> 00:08.800
[samba music playing]

00:11.320 --> 00:12.960
[whistle trilling]

00:13.040 --> 00:15.240
[samba music continuing]

00:37.960 --> 00:40.360
[whistle trilling rhythmically]

00:45.000 --> 00:47.440
[ululating]

00:51.120 --> 00:52.400
[in English] He's crazy.

00:58.640 --> 01:01.200
I'm glad you turned out to be
the mellow brother, you know.

01:01.280 --> 01:03.080
Yeah. Me, too.

01:07.080 --> 01:12.600
And, uh, you look even more beautiful
in real life than on the profile picture.

01:15.040 --> 01:17.240
It's usually the other way around,
you know?

01:18.240 --> 01:21.480
Yeah, yeah. It usually is.

01:24.720 --> 01:26.360
[music ends]

01:28.920 --> 01:30.880
[dancer] Yeah. Very good.

01:30.960 --> 01:32.040
Really good.

01:32.120 --> 01:33.520
[dancer] Really good.

01:34.520 --> 01:36.640
- Are you okay?
- [Torgeir] Yes.

01:36.720 --> 01:38.280
[Roar] Jesus.

01:38.360 --> 01:40.560
[in Brazilian Portuguese]
Oh! Cheers! Cheers!

01:47.040 --> 01:50.080
- [Norwegian] Isn't Alex joining us?
- She said she was too tired.

01:50.160 --> 01:52.120
You have a Brazilian girlfriend!

01:52.200 --> 01:53.920
- It's insane.
- What are the odds?

01:54.000 --> 01:57.960
- I know. Me, of all people.
- They're nothing like our local girls.

01:58.040 --> 01:59.200
[Roar] I know.

02:00.680 --> 02:04.760
[in English] Hey, hey. My man, my friend.
What's up, my friend?

02:04.840 --> 02:06.520
Where are you from?

02:06.600 --> 02:07.800
Norway.

02:07.880 --> 02:08.880
Norway.

02:08.960 --> 02:11.720
- Yeah, Norway T-shirt, 1998.
- I like it. Yeah.

02:11.800 --> 02:15.040
Ninety-eight? And would you guys happen
to have some money to give us?

02:16.080 --> 02:17.160
Uh, no.

02:17.240 --> 02:19.480
- [man] You don't have money?
- [man 2] No money?

02:19.560 --> 02:21.600
- No, not on us.
- No?

02:21.680 --> 02:23.280
How about give me the money?

02:23.360 --> 02:24.440
Give me the money, huh?

02:24.520 --> 02:25.640
Give me the money.

02:25.720 --> 02:27.720
Give me the fucking money.

02:27.800 --> 02:30.560
- Wow, yeah, okay, okay.
- I want all of this shit.

02:30.640 --> 02:32.560
[in English]
Take it. We have it here.

02:32.640 --> 02:34.080
[in Norwegian]
Go on and give it to him.

02:34.160 --> 02:35.440
[in Brazilian Portuguese]
Is that all? Nothing more?

02:35.520 --> 02:36.920
Give it back.

02:37.000 --> 02:38.400
Give it back!

02:38.480 --> 02:39.880
What the fuck are you doing?

02:39.960 --> 02:42.800
Shit, it's Oscarito.
He owns Morro da BabilÃ´nia.

02:42.880 --> 02:45.480
Okay. Everything is all right. No worries.

02:51.360 --> 02:55.360
[in English] So, are you guys coming
for the after-party or not?

02:55.440 --> 02:56.640
[Roar chuckles]

02:58.120 --> 03:00.360
What the...? How did you...?

03:02.880 --> 03:05.880
[theme music playing]

03:38.400 --> 03:41.120
[distant church bells ringing]

03:41.200 --> 03:44.200
[Christmas carols playing
in Norwegian over PA]

03:55.160 --> 03:58.040
With my sincerest gratitude,
this New Year's Eve,

03:58.120 --> 04:01.040
I wish to share some reflections
I have made so far in life,

04:01.120 --> 04:04.680
related to us as individuals,
and as a nation.

04:04.760 --> 04:06.800
[violin playing "Auld Lang Syne"]

04:06.880 --> 04:10.520
No one can live
an entire life without love.

04:10.600 --> 04:13.360
- [chuckles]
- [phone rings]

04:13.440 --> 04:14.240
Yeah.

04:14.320 --> 04:17.640
[Torgeir in English]  Hi. I'm just calling
to say thank you for the old year.

04:17.720 --> 04:20.080
Hey, happy New Year to you, too.

04:20.160 --> 04:22.440
How's your brother holding up?
Is he ready for his big day?

04:22.520 --> 04:23.520
Yeah, he's, uh...

04:23.600 --> 04:24.600
[in Norwegian] ...getting there.

04:24.680 --> 04:28.600
Guess what?
We almost got mugged last night.

04:28.680 --> 04:29.680
Uh-huh.

04:29.760 --> 04:32.240
We were out walking
when suddenly two guys came along

04:32.320 --> 04:35.040
and one of them pulled a gun on us.

04:35.120 --> 04:40.000
I was sure that it was all over.

04:40.080 --> 04:42.440
For me, at least.

04:42.520 --> 04:47.680
But then Oscarito,
Roar's future brother-in-law, comes up.

04:47.760 --> 04:50.520
And he looks at the robbers
and says,  "Habla, habla, habla" --

04:50.600 --> 04:53.080
[in English] Uh...
Listen, I gotta call you back.

04:54.080 --> 04:56.920
[in Norwegian]  Two hundred years ago,
a group of men gathered at Eidsvoll

04:57.000 --> 04:59.800
to create what we today
know as our constitution...

05:02.960 --> 05:07.200
Our constitution has evolved
over time...

05:07.280 --> 05:09.000
[Johnny yells]

05:09.080 --> 05:10.360
Open the door!

05:10.440 --> 05:12.480
[in Norwegian]
We're closed.

05:12.560 --> 05:13.840
[in English]
Emergency!

05:13.920 --> 05:17.160
- [banging on door]
- Open it up!

05:18.760 --> 05:20.040
Fuck.

05:27.720 --> 05:29.320
Where's the keys?

05:29.840 --> 05:31.560
- Um...
- I'll deal with you later.

05:34.800 --> 05:37.680
- [Andrius] You want more?
- [woman crying]

05:37.760 --> 05:39.680
[Johnny] Hey.

05:39.760 --> 05:41.880
Let her go, you fucking animal.

05:42.560 --> 05:43.960
Oh, yeah?

05:46.080 --> 05:48.200
[liquid bubbling]

05:50.840 --> 05:53.280
[screams]

05:54.600 --> 05:55.960
[Andrius] Momma!

05:56.040 --> 05:58.200
[howls in pain]

05:58.280 --> 06:00.360
- [Andrius] Fuck you!
- [Johnny] You all right?

06:00.440 --> 06:02.320
[Andrius] Fuck you... [screams]

06:02.400 --> 06:03.880
- [gun cocks]
- [Johnny] Fuck.

06:03.960 --> 06:07.160
[in Lithuanian]
Mom, what are you waiting for? Shoot.

06:07.880 --> 06:09.880
[gunshots echo]

06:45.440 --> 06:47.680
[tiger snarling]

06:48.880 --> 06:52.600
[growling]

06:59.280 --> 07:01.280
[sirens wailing]

07:05.680 --> 07:07.080
[woman in Norwegian]
Prep him for surgery.

07:07.160 --> 07:09.360
[man] A man in his 50s has been shot.

07:09.440 --> 07:11.320
- [woman] Ready?
- [woman 2] Ready.

07:11.400 --> 07:13.760
- What's going on?
- [man] You must wait here.

07:13.840 --> 07:15.080
[Arne] Is he alive?

07:16.280 --> 07:18.760
[woman]
He's not stable. We're losing him.

07:22.680 --> 07:26.320
- [Arne] Did he say anything to you?
- He was out of it.

07:26.400 --> 07:30.360
He said something about a cheerleader
and a one-armed lady.

07:34.120 --> 07:37.760
[woman] Blood pressure is dropping.
He's not stable. He's going into shock.

07:41.080 --> 07:43.240
[heart monitor beeping]

07:43.320 --> 07:45.400
[growls]

07:48.120 --> 07:51.160
- [man] Get him out of here!
- [in English] Let him stay.

07:51.240 --> 07:53.120
[man in English]
No, he doesn't belong here.

07:53.200 --> 07:55.840
- [Johnny] Who the fuck does?
- [growls]

07:55.920 --> 07:58.600
[man] Prepare to defibrillate.

08:13.120 --> 08:16.600
[slow Latin jazz playing]

08:17.880 --> 08:20.480
[crackling, popping]

08:28.600 --> 08:30.720
[Jesus in Brazilian Portuguese]
Dear family...

08:31.960 --> 08:33.560
...dear friends,

08:33.640 --> 08:37.400
we live in stormy times.

08:37.480 --> 08:40.640
We were overjoyed
when we got broadband,

08:40.720 --> 08:43.480
thanks to the Olympic
development plan in Rio.

08:45.000 --> 08:48.480
But a few hours
in a chat room, and presto,

08:48.560 --> 08:49.960
my daughter...

08:50.960 --> 08:54.160
...a beautiful and talented
economics student...

08:57.280 --> 09:00.760
...is now engaged
to a simple truck driver from Norway.

09:02.360 --> 09:04.760
Please, Dad, not now.

09:07.000 --> 09:10.960
And who am I
to speak of your future destiny?

09:11.040 --> 09:13.640
- [phone ringing]
- [in Norwegian] Oops, that's my phone.

09:13.720 --> 09:16.440
- Just turn it off.
- But it's for me.

09:16.520 --> 09:18.720
- [in English] Sorry. Sorry.
- [in Norwegian] Don't answer it.

09:18.800 --> 09:21.840
- Hi, Roy.
- [Roar] Don't answer it!

09:22.680 --> 09:25.320
[in English] I'm really, really sorry
about my brother.

09:25.400 --> 09:27.800
He's always so busy, but...

09:27.880 --> 09:29.440
Cheers to Alex.

09:29.520 --> 09:31.240
[in Norwegian]
What did you just say?

09:33.560 --> 09:37.640
But when? How? Who did this?

09:48.880 --> 09:50.280
I'm leaving.

09:51.000 --> 09:52.480
- Really?
- Yeah.

09:52.560 --> 09:54.960
Right before your brother's wedding?

09:55.040 --> 09:56.320
Nice.

09:57.600 --> 09:59.960
Johnny has been shot.

10:00.040 --> 10:02.880
He needs me. He could die.

10:02.960 --> 10:04.280
I understand that.

10:04.360 --> 10:07.640
But maybe someone else
needs a certain someone

10:07.720 --> 10:10.440
on an important day in his life.

10:10.520 --> 10:12.400
How would you feel if you got shot?

10:13.400 --> 10:15.600
[scoffs]

10:15.680 --> 10:17.600
Not everything is about you.

10:20.480 --> 10:22.560
Who the hell is going to be
my best man now?

10:24.800 --> 10:26.120
[Torgeir] Sorry.

10:31.960 --> 10:35.240
[in English]
Can you do my back with this cream?

10:36.680 --> 10:38.280
No, thanks.

10:38.960 --> 10:41.560
I leave the dirty work to my sister.

11:02.280 --> 11:06.040
[train rumbling]

11:10.600 --> 11:14.000
[Turbonegro's "Age of Pamparius" playing]

11:23.360 --> 11:24.640
[air hissing]

11:33.920 --> 11:36.120
[crashing]

11:47.040 --> 11:49.920
[ice creaking, groaning]

12:09.480 --> 12:11.040
[Dag in Norwegian]  Hi.

12:11.120 --> 12:13.920
This is Dag Solstad.

12:14.000 --> 12:16.200
I'd like to report an accident.

12:16.280 --> 12:20.960
The thing is,
I was driving down the highway.

12:21.040 --> 12:24.040
And the road was really slippery.

12:24.120 --> 12:27.160
The truck started skidding, and...

12:28.160 --> 12:31.640
And I drove straight out onto the ice.

12:32.640 --> 12:34.840
[bottles clinking]

12:35.840 --> 12:39.080
COUNTY HOSPITAL

12:44.840 --> 12:46.760
[bags clattering]

13:00.240 --> 13:02.240
[sniffs]

13:02.320 --> 13:04.400
[sobs]

13:10.560 --> 13:13.400
[in English]
You're in a better place now, Johnny.

13:14.040 --> 13:15.160
[wheels squeaking]

13:15.240 --> 13:17.280
[Johnny] Better than what?

13:19.640 --> 13:21.000
You're alive!

13:23.120 --> 13:25.800
You're alive. Thank God.

13:25.880 --> 13:27.920
- Easy, killer. Easy, easy.
- Sorry.

13:28.000 --> 13:29.920
- It's okay.
- I thought you were dead.

13:30.920 --> 13:32.440
[cries] I'm so happy.

13:32.520 --> 13:37.400
Hi, Johnny. I brought a little
get-well present from my greenhouse.

13:37.480 --> 13:38.520
[Johnny] It's nice.

13:39.760 --> 13:41.680
What else you bring me?

13:41.760 --> 13:44.920
[in Norwegian] We found out
that Mesna Chess Club

13:45.000 --> 13:47.880
had ordered a cheerleader striptease.

13:47.960 --> 13:51.880
The stripper didn't show,
but they were from the Baltics.

13:52.880 --> 13:56.960
So we're talking
Lithuania or Estragonia?

13:58.960 --> 14:05.920
Once we find those Stalinist pigs,
I'll disembowel every one of--

14:07.120 --> 14:10.080
- [Sigrid in English] Hi! How are you?
- [Johnny] Hi, honey. How are you?

14:10.160 --> 14:11.160
Ooh. I'm all right.

14:11.240 --> 14:12.720
[in Norwegian]
Want to give these to Daddy?

14:12.800 --> 14:14.760
Hi, baby. How are you?

14:14.840 --> 14:16.040
[in English]
But you're doing okay?

14:16.120 --> 14:18.560
[Johnny] Yeah, I'm all right.
Except for the food.

14:18.640 --> 14:21.520
- [Sigrid] Oh, yeah.
- [Johnny] You didn't bring me lasagna?

14:21.600 --> 14:24.960
[in Norwegian] I told them
that Daddy had appendicitis.

14:26.280 --> 14:27.720
Good to see you up, Johnny.

14:27.800 --> 14:31.840
