15:01.320 --> 15:02.440
Hi.

15:02.520 --> 15:05.280
[in Norwegian]
Right, how can I help you?

15:05.360 --> 15:07.680
Regarding the room situation
for Henriksen...

15:07.760 --> 15:09.320
- [doctor] Yes?
- The gun victim.

15:10.320 --> 15:11.720
Yes?

15:11.800 --> 15:15.480
Henriksen is
a celebrated nightclub entrepreneur.

15:15.560 --> 15:21.800
It isn't appropriate for him
to be in a ward full of vegetables.

15:22.880 --> 15:24.320
Vegetables?

15:24.400 --> 15:26.480
The demented,
if that's what you call them.

15:26.560 --> 15:31.000
Yes, that's what we say.
Doesn't Henriksen have a single room?

15:31.080 --> 15:33.360
Yes, but--

15:33.440 --> 15:37.200
Then he has no reason to complain.

15:37.280 --> 15:38.720
There's nothing more I can do.

15:39.720 --> 15:40.720
Okay?

15:43.400 --> 15:47.120
I can tell that you're stressed.
A busy lady.

15:50.000 --> 15:52.400
In which case,
there could be nothing better...

15:53.720 --> 15:55.760
...than winding down with a lovely cigar.

15:57.520 --> 15:59.880
I scratch your back, you scratch mine.

16:02.520 --> 16:06.200
Are you trying to bribe me
with carcinogenic contraband?

16:07.800 --> 16:09.000
Correct.

16:19.200 --> 16:23.520
Tell Mr. Negotiator to put
the tomato plant on the table.

16:23.600 --> 16:25.640
I'm not speaking to him at the moment.

16:32.840 --> 16:34.200
Hi.

16:34.280 --> 16:37.400
[Torgeir in Norwegian] How sure are we
these are the guys that shot Johnny?

16:37.480 --> 16:42.760
They were at the diner
on New Year's Eve, and they spoke Baltic.

16:42.840 --> 16:46.800
- And their clothes were bloodied.
- I'll bet that was Johnny's blood!

16:46.880 --> 16:48.600
- [Roy] Yes.
- It has to be his blood.

16:48.680 --> 16:51.080
- [Roy] Exactly. Okay.
- Let's get those bastards!

16:51.160 --> 16:55.280
- Come on, boys! Let's rock and roll.
- Yeah! Come on!

16:55.360 --> 16:56.400
We'll show them...

16:57.400 --> 16:58.640
...blood!

17:04.200 --> 17:07.880
[speaking Polish] Come on, faster.
They need that meat.

17:10.520 --> 17:13.240
[in Norwegian] Christ,
what kind of sick operation is this?

17:13.320 --> 17:14.880
[in Polish] Come on.

17:14.960 --> 17:16.400
[in Norwegian]
This is just like  Dexter .

17:16.480 --> 17:19.880
[electric saw buzzing]

17:23.520 --> 17:25.360
[Roy] Okay, guys.

17:25.440 --> 17:26.440
Come on!

17:27.600 --> 17:28.920
For Johnny!

17:29.920 --> 17:31.440
Come on, guys!

17:38.720 --> 17:41.440
[man in Polish]
We must get moving.

17:41.520 --> 17:43.520
Hurry up.

18:00.200 --> 18:03.920
[Torgeir in English] Okay, everybody.
Don't fucking move!

18:04.000 --> 18:06.560
[Roy] Where is the one-armed lady?

18:06.640 --> 18:07.920
[Torgeir] Where?

18:19.560 --> 18:21.600
[Roy in Norwegian]
Salami? Huh?

18:23.160 --> 18:24.240
What the fuck?

18:25.240 --> 18:27.440
What the hell's going on here?

18:27.520 --> 18:30.560
Uh... [stammering]

18:33.200 --> 18:35.200
We're from the Food Safety Authority.

18:35.280 --> 18:37.200
My Poles are legal.

18:41.160 --> 18:42.760
[Torgeir] Yes.

18:42.840 --> 18:44.880
Everything looks okay here.

18:44.960 --> 18:46.560
Let's move on, guys.

18:46.640 --> 18:48.280
Have a nice day.

18:58.000 --> 19:00.680
[man singing Norwegian ballad over radio]

19:13.040 --> 19:15.360
Mind if I, uh, turn off the light?

19:23.280 --> 19:24.480
[Johnny sighs]

19:25.800 --> 19:27.840
[man] I saw the tiger, too.

19:31.000 --> 19:32.240
Come again?

19:33.040 --> 19:35.720
I saw the tiger, too.

19:39.360 --> 19:41.280
I sure hope this is a dream.

19:41.360 --> 19:44.680
It's all a dream, Silvio.

19:45.680 --> 19:48.120
It's all a dream.

20:05.160 --> 20:06.840
Ladies.

20:08.000 --> 20:10.120
[chuckles]

20:10.200 --> 20:12.080
[boy muttering]

20:17.720 --> 20:21.960
CHILDREN'S PSYCHIATRIC UNIT

20:37.240 --> 20:38.800
AUTISTIC - NON-COMMUNICATIVE
TRAUMATIZED AFTER SHOOTING

20:38.880 --> 20:40.600
That's who you are.

20:44.080 --> 20:47.080
Hiya, tiger. Remember me?

20:48.960 --> 20:51.320
I want to thank you
for looking after me out there.

20:54.560 --> 20:56.680
The strong silent type, eh?

20:58.200 --> 20:59.440
That's all right.

21:00.360 --> 21:03.560
You saw me get shot, you remember that?

21:04.600 --> 21:06.080
Well, look at me now.

21:06.160 --> 21:07.840
Good as new.

21:08.840 --> 21:11.320
[Magnus] "Look,
I know you're a smart lawyer.

21:11.400 --> 21:14.400
Don't get smart with me."

21:14.480 --> 21:16.160
What's that you say?

21:19.040 --> 21:22.200
Oh! Why don't you sit down,
Johnny, have a cookie?

21:22.280 --> 21:24.080
All right, don't mind if I do.

21:24.160 --> 21:27.000
[chuckles]

21:27.080 --> 21:28.080
[Magnus whines]

21:28.160 --> 21:31.200
What? All right.
All right. Those are yours.

21:32.120 --> 21:34.800
Uh... This one's all right?

21:34.880 --> 21:35.880
[Magnus] Mmm.

21:38.200 --> 21:41.200
"Laury Martin?
That little fresh kid with the pigtails?"

21:43.000 --> 21:45.040
Are you speaking my language there, tiger?

21:46.040 --> 21:48.480
"Morning, gentlemen.
Nice day for a murder.

21:48.560 --> 21:52.440
Where's Frazier? Where's the hundred
grand? You think we're gonna pay off?"

21:53.480 --> 21:57.360
That's  Angels with Dirty Faces ,
my favorite Jimmy Cagney movie.

21:58.800 --> 22:03.440
Now, try this on for size:
"Waddaya hear, waddaya say?"

22:05.240 --> 22:09.240
"Waddaya hear, waddaya say?
I'm glad to see you, Rocky."

22:09.320 --> 22:14.520
"Oh, and I'm glad to see you too, kiddo.
I'm glad to see you."

22:14.600 --> 22:16.600
[chuckles]

22:28.200 --> 22:31.840
[in Norwegian] How did you do that?
He never speaks to strangers.

22:31.920 --> 22:34.480
[in English] Turns out,
we have very similar taste in movies.

22:34.560 --> 22:36.000
Movies?

22:36.080 --> 22:37.560
[Johnny] Mm-hmm.

22:37.640 --> 22:38.720
All that mumbling...

22:38.800 --> 22:39.800
Yeah, yeah...

22:39.880 --> 22:42.000
Old gangster movies.

22:44.440 --> 22:46.120
Go figure.

22:49.000 --> 22:51.720
[in Norwegian]
Henriksen, what are you doing here?

22:52.560 --> 22:55.240
We have to redress your wound.

22:55.320 --> 22:56.400
[in English]
It sounds wonderful,

22:56.480 --> 22:59.000
but I was just having a conversation
with the tiger boy in there

22:59.080 --> 23:00.840
and, uh, we had quite a breakthrough.

23:00.920 --> 23:05.200
Turns out that he's a big fan
of the old gangster movies.

23:05.280 --> 23:07.800
I was wondering if you had
any of those channels

23:07.880 --> 23:10.240
that show those old gangster movies.

23:10.320 --> 23:12.160
Or I could maybe donate a satellite.

23:12.240 --> 23:16.360
[in Norwegian]
No. We prefer NRK.

23:16.440 --> 23:20.040
There's so much violence
on the other channels.

23:20.120 --> 23:21.120
[in English]
Are you kidding me?

23:21.200 --> 23:24.040
